I am writing about a property in {{ county_name }} County, California that may have generated excess proceeds after a tax-defaulted property sale. Under California Revenue and Taxation Code Sections 4671 through 4675, excess proceeds are the funds remaining after the county applies the sale proceeds to delinquent taxes, penalties, costs, and other amounts allowed by law.

Here are the details from the public record:

